The Executive Director of Human Development Initiatives HDI, Mrs Olufunsho Owasanoye has called on Chief Executive Officers of companies and parastatals to adopt emotional intelligence to enhance team work among their subordinates. Owasanoye stated this recently in Lagos at a two-day capacity building for Education Secretaries across the state. The HDI boss noted that managing other peoples’ emotions is practically impossible if one cannot manage his own emotion first, on how to relate and talk with one’s subordinates.   ‘Why Nigeria witnesses more flight cancellations,…     Expert mulls support for tourism development     BEDC lauds community over vandals’ arrest   Mrs Owasanoye who opined that respect should be earned and not demanded tasked the chief executives to erase attitude of domineering and work as a team with their subordinates to achieve their objectives. She observed that the training for the education secretaries is necessary being the people at helm of affairs to re-orient them on the strategic management in terms of efficiency and effectiveness in basic education in Lagos state - Advertisement - She added that education secretaries are the foundation and building blocks of the education sector, hence the need to build their capacity for effective and efficient delivery of the teaching-learning process.